The Biden-Harris Administration has released a Root Causes Strategy aimed at addressing the root causes of migration from El Salvador, Guatemala, and Honduras. Vice President Kamala Harris has been leading diplomatic efforts to improve security, governance, human rights, and economic conditions in the region. The strategy integrates various tools such as diplomacy, foreign assistance, public diplomacy, and sanctions. Implementation will involve collaboration with U.S. departments and agencies, governments, civil society, the private sector, multilateral organizations, international financial institutions, and the U.S. Congress. The strategy focuses on targeted areas where migrants are most likely to come from and is organized into five pillars. Notable accomplishments have already been made, and the full report can be found at the provided link.